Class CostBuildingGoodsService

java.lang.Object
com.example.paragonPioneerBackend.Service.generic.BaseService<CostBuildingGoods,CostBuildingGoodsRepository,CostBuildingGoodsInput>
com.example.paragonPioneerBackend.Service.CostBuildingGoodsService
@Service public class CostBuildingGoodsService extends BaseService<CostBuildingGoods,CostBuildingGoodsRepository,CostBuildingGoodsInput>
Service class for managing the relationships between buildings and goods within the application. This class extends the BaseService to offer specialized CRUD operations for the Cost_Building_Goods entity. It interacts with the GoodRepository and BuildingRepository to handle operations related to building costs and goods.

    • patch

      @Transactional public CostBuildingGoods patch(CostBuildingGoods entityToUpdate, CostBuildingGoodsInput costBuildingGoodsDTO)
      This method is used to update the properties of a Cost_Building_Goods entity based on the provided DTO. It updates the building, good, and amount of the entity to update. The building and good are updated using the PatchUtil.patchHelper method, which checks if the new value is null. If the new value is not null, it replaces the old value. If it is null, the old value is kept. The amount is updated directly from the DTO.
      Specified by:
      patch in class BaseService<CostBuildingGoods,CostBuildingGoodsRepository,CostBuildingGoodsInput>
      Parameters:
      entityToUpdate - The original Cost_Building_Goods entity that might be updated.
      costBuildingGoodsDTO - The DTO that contains the new values for the Cost_Building_Goods entity.
      Returns:
      The updated Cost_Building_Goods entity.
